  {
    "id": "c5fc1cc7-1d4e-492b-bb3d-b5d748dc9565",
    "sentence": "Today the Committee has further revised its forward guidance to better reflect conditions as they now stand and are likely to evolve over coming quarters. The revised formulation starts with a general description of the factors that drive FOMC decisionmaking and then provides the FOMC's current assessment of what those factors will likely imply for the future path of short- term interest rates.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140319.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "db312f0f-a2a4-4e5a-9cb6-ecd155d5bc04",
    "sentence": "Although FOMC participants provide a number of explanations for the federal funds rate running below its longer-run normal level at that time, many cite the residual effects of the financial crisis, which, although slowly diminishing, are likely to continue to restrain household spending, constrain credit availability, and depress expectations for future growth in output and incomes.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140917.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140917",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "36e9b697-eb3a-4ed1-a9bd-4665b27964cf",
    "sentence": "But, as the last phrase of the enhanced guidance underscores, the prospects for inflation provide another reason to keep policy accommodative.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20131218.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20131218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f1afc90f-6574-49bd-9dab-b7d1f4b99f49",
    "sentence": "Conditions in the labor market appear to be gradually cooling, and inflation remains somewhat elevated.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20251210.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20251210",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "967332bc-58f2-4f2f-ac2b-fbcc063286fc",
    "sentence": "Activity in the housing sector has weakened significantly, in large part reflecting higher mortgage rates.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220921.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220921",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "92904e29-f8af-4852-88e4-b14c9854d354",
    "sentence": "We continue to believe that a gradual approach for increasing the federal funds rate will best promote a sustained expansion of economic activity, strong labor market conditions, and inflation near our symmetric 2 percent goal.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20180613.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20180613",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f1837386-0522-4a62-aa08-d737dfc088fa",
    "sentence": "We stated that, subject to our ongoing assessment of the efficacy and costs of the program, purchases would continue until we saw a substantial improvement in the outlook for the labor market in a context of price stability.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b07a898d-e731-4a67-a2a7-27e7f6a8a316",
    "sentence": "Inflation has remained low and stable and is ending the year a bit more subdued than most had expected.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20181219.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20181219",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6fc9a0fe-74f6-4eab-bc7b-e0430f745a63",
    "sentence": "The unemployment rate projections for this year are a little higher than in March.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20150617.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20150617",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e75b317a-1759-47da-aa72-386ddda70af7",
    "sentence": "The federal funds rate is now in the broad range of estimates of neutral -- the rate that tends neither to stimulate nor to restrain the economy.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "eb84b03a-c30f-4bce-916a-cce54d381b96",
    "sentence": "Unusually strong payroll job growth in January was followed by little growth at all in February.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ff10f094-a880-4fd5-88a9-d9ec09f327bd",
    "sentence": "The median participant projects that the appropriate level of the federal funds rate will be 3.9 percent at the end of next year and 3.4 percent at the end of 2026.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20241218.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20241218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4fc7517e-8a5b-4d35-a960-8848621e564c",
    "sentence": "However, even after asset purchases are wound down -- which we will do in a manner that is both deliberate and dependent on the incoming economic data -- the Federal Reserve's rates guidance and its ongoing holdings of securities will ensure that monetary policy remains highly accommodative, consistent with an aggressive pursuit of our mandated objectives of maximum employment and price stability.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3d78e98f-6bbd-4d09-bc8e-919166de28c4",
    "sentence": "Returning to monetary policy, as I noted at the outset, the Committee reaffirmed its view that the current 0 to ¼ percent target range for the federal funds rate remains appropriate. But with economic conditions improving, and with further improvement expected in the months ahead, we have again modified our forward guidance.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20150318.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20150318",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "45a14dd2-a1d4-4708-9ac9-0072e122b8a0",
    "sentence": "In particular, the high level of joblessness has been especially severe for lower-wage workers in the service sector and for African Americans and Hispanics.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210428.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210428",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9261bf31-79d2-4d49-b30d-8183b0b9b6b2",
    "sentence": "The Committee moved from expecting rate increases this year to a patient stance about any changes and then to today's action.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190731.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5234dac1-cdaf-4807-a706-44ae9f49cbcc",
    "sentence": "The future course of monetary policy will depend on how the economy evolves and what developments imply for the economic outlook and risks to the outlook. We have often said that policy is not on a preset course, and that is certainly the case today.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "675b5594-6ded-4dd4-b048-fe0e7e6c1593",
    "sentence": "Since March, progress on vaccinations has limited the number of new cases, hospitalizations, and deaths.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210428.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210428",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e43f2444-7e7a-4f83-aeeb-fff67d9574af",
    "sentence": "At the FOMC meeting that concluded today, we reviewed economic and financial developments in the United States and around the world and decided to leave our policy interest rate unchanged.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190501.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ca9aac6b-1f59-46ab-918e-e13ea2b320bd",
    "sentence": "Growth in household spending slowed, business fixed investment edged down, and net exports were a substantial drag on growth.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20150617.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20150617",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6111cdf8-8a09-4e9f-85a7-d475c214318f",
    "sentence": "Job gains in April and May are estimated to have averaged only about 80,000 per month. And while the unemployment rate fell to 4.7 percent in May, that decline occurred because fewer people reported that they were actively seeking work.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160615.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7048f45e-5986-4f58-b2f5-39486e1c22d2",
    "sentence": "The unemployment rate fell to 4.6 percent in November, the lowest level since 2007, prior to the recession.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20161214.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20161214",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a2a3d904-44ee-4b01-bd1b-4cf403667cb1",
    "sentence": "Given that the Committee is not signaling a change in policy, why did we update our guidance?",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20141217.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20141217",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9fd29aa0-b3cc-4143-9be5-99ca658db7da",
    "sentence": "At our June meeting, many Committee participants saw that the case for lowering the federal funds rate had strengthened, but the Committee wanted to get a better sense of the overall direction of events.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190731.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "567a5570-9920-4efe-b8eb-fa1222d734e5",
    "sentence": "Inflation has been running below the Committee's longer-run objective of 2 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20131218.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20131218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b714b881-e9e9-47eb-b2d0-76ffd18d0a2d",
    "sentence": "We're strongly committed to achieving our symmetric 2 percent inflation goal.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20191211.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20191211",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "23b5cb59-3bf2-4846-bcc1-f2676b60b92b",
    "sentence": "Inflation continues to run below our symmetric 2 percent objective.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20191211.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20191211",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e8c57149-cf0d-4a8a-ae47-dcc58d82e698",
    "sentence": "I will have more to say about monetary policy after briefly reviewing economic developments.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20251029.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20251029",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d742ef5b-6b11-4c1c-833a-e551e0e2da7b",
    "sentence": "Even after today's action takes effect, we will continue to significantly expand our holdings of longer-term securities, and we will also continue to roll over maturing Treasury securities and reinvest principal payments from the FOMC's holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140319.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
