  {
    "id": "c0536cb1-e309-44c8-ae72-a102451653b6",
    "sentence": "One indication that the neutral funds rate is unusually low is that U.S. economic growth has been only moderate in recent years despite the very low level of the federal funds rate and the Federal Reserve's very large holdings of longer- term securities. Had the neutral rate been running closer to its longer-run level, these policy actions would have been expected to foster a much more rapid economic expansion.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20151216.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20151216",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dd4044b2-eab7-4407-807b-3d882edbcbb2",
    "sentence": "In the near term, risks to inflation are tilted to the upside and risks to employment to the downside -- a challenging situation.",
